    <string name="gms_cap_push">Push notifications (FCM / GCM)</string>
    <string name="gms_cap_push_desc">Server-sent notifications (messaging, alerts) may be delayed or not arrive without Google Play services or microG. The app still launches and works with manual refresh.</string>
    <string name="gms_cap_activity">Activity recognition / step counter</string>
    <string name="gms_cap_activity_desc">Activity and step detection go through Play services. Without it (microG does not provide this), these fitness features do not work.</string>
    <string name="gms_cap_maps">Embedded Google Maps</string>
    <string name="gms_cap_maps_desc">An embedded Google Maps view may stay grey or blank without Google Play services. microG covers it partially.</string>
    <string name="gms_cap_billing">Google Play purchases and subscriptions</string>
    <string name="gms_cap_billing_desc">In-app purchases and subscriptions go through the Play Store. Without it (microG does not replace it), purchases fail. The app often stays usable in its free version.</string>
    <string name="gms_cap_licensing">Google Play licence check (LVL)</string>
    <string name="gms_cap_licensing_desc">The app checks its licence with the Play Store. Without it the check fails; depending on the app this ranges from a reminder to refusing to start.</string>
    <string name="gms_cap_signin">Google sign-in (legacy auth token)</string>
    <string name="gms_cap_signin_desc">Signing in with a Google account uses a Google service that is absent without Play services. It is often one sign-in option among others.</string>
    <string name="gms_cap_maps_v1">Google Maps v1 (legacy system library)</string>
    <string name="gms_cap_maps_v1_desc">This app uses the legacy Google Maps v1 library, absent on de-Googled devices and not provided by microG (its servers were shut down in 2013). Map screens may crash.</string>
    <string name="allow_unknown_sources">Allow installing apps</string>
    <string name="allow_unknown_sources_DESC">Omnify needs permission to install apps. Allow it now so you\'re not interrupted at your first install.\n\nAfter you enable it in settings, Android closes Omnify to apply the change (especially on TV). This is normal: just reopen the app.</string>
